-- Russia Equity Movers: Mechel, Novatek, Sberbank, Rostelecom
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-10T15:56:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/russia-equity-movers-mechel-novatek-sberbank-rostelecom.html
The 30-stock Micex Index rose 1.8
percent to 1,408.31 by the close in Moscow, snapping six days of
declines.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Mechel (MTLR)   increased 5.4 percent to 229.20
rubles, the biggest gain since Jan. 26.  Russia ’s largest
producer of coal for steelmakers said profit in the fourth
quarter surged almost eightfold as the ruble strengthened,
leading to a foreign exchange gain.  OAO Novatek (NVTK RX) added 5.5 percent to 333.52 rubles,
the strongest advance since July 21.  Alfa Bank  forecast 11
percent sales growth in the first quarter from a year earlier
for Russia’s second-largest natural-gas producer.  OAO Rostelecom (RTKM RX), Russia’s long-distance phone
operator, gained 2.2 percent to 127.86 rubles. Vedomosti
reported President  Vladimir Putin  ordered the completion of its
merger with OAO Svyazinvest, the national telecommunications
holding.  OAO Sberbank (SBER RX) climbed 2.7 percent to 91.74 rubles.
Russia’s biggest lender said it increased profit by about 14
percent in the first four months of the year.  United Co. Rusal (RUALR RX) fell 1.3 percent to 196.98
rubles, the lowest level since Jan. 10.  Renaissance Capital 
forecast a 5 percent decline in first-quarter margins from the
previous three-month period at the world’s largest aluminum
producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
